Introduction to EDUCE

The Experiential Data science for Undergraduate Cross-disciplinary Education (EDUCE) initiative at the U. of British Columbia creates flexible curriculum in data science. This includes Unix command line, R/RStudio, statistics, and next-generation sequencing analyses. While EDUCE was originally designed for integration into undergraduate microbiology courses at UBC, the content is broadly applicable across many disciplines.

This document was created using our Course Compiler. Thus, it contains only the courses and content that were selected for inclusion by the user. All our course and workshop materials can also be found on the EDUCE GitHub.
